$
\left|\begin{array}{ccccc}
x+1 & x & x & \cdots & x\\
x & x+2 & x & \cdots & x\\
x &x & x+3 & \cdots &x\\
\cdots & \cdots & \cdots & \cdots & \cdots\\
x&  x & x & \cdots & x+n\end{array}\right| \sim 

\left|\begin{array}{ccccc}
1 & 0 & 0 & \cdots & -n\\
0 & 2 & 0 & \cdots & -n\\
0 &0 & 3 & \cdots &-n\\
\cdots & \cdots & \cdots & \cdots & \cdots\\
x&  x & x & \cdots & x+n\end{array}\right|=\\
=x\left|\begin{array}{cccc}
0 & 0 & \cdots & -n \\
2 & 0 & \cdots & -n \\
0 & 3 & \cdots & -n \\
\cdots & \cdots & \cdots & \cdots \\
0 & 0 & \cdots & -n \end{array}\right|+(-1)^{(n-1)}
\left|\begin{array}{cccc}
2 & 0 & \cdots & -n\\
0 & 3 & \cdots & -n\\
0 & 0 & \cdots & -n\\
\cdots & \cdots & \cdots & \cdots\\
x & x & \cdots & x+n\end{array}\right|=\\
=x(1 \cdot 2 \cdot ... \cdot n)+1(1 \cdot 2 \cdot ... \cdot n)+x(1 \cdot 3 \cdot 4 \cdot ... \cdot n) + x(1 \cdot 2 \cdot 3 \cdot 5 \cdot ... \cdot n) + ... + x(1 \cdot 2 \cdot ... \cdot (n-1))=\\
=(1 \cdot 2 \cdot ... \cdot n)(1+x+\frac{x}{2}+\frac{x}{3}+...+\frac{x}{n})


$
